ğŸ“Œ Project Overview

The Nutrition Paradox project analyzes the coexistence of rising obesity and persistent malnutrition across countries, regions, age groups, and genders using WHO public health datasets.
The project applies ETL, data cleaning, SQL analytics, EDA, and visualization to uncover global nutrition trends and support data-driven public health decision-making.

ğŸ¯ Problem Statement

As a Data Analyst for a global health organization, the objective is to investigate how undernutrition and overnutrition vary worldwide.
Using publicly available WHO data, the project explores:

Country-wise and regional trends

Adult vs child nutrition patterns

Gender disparities

Changes over time (2012â€“2022)

The goal is to derive actionable insights that can guide policy planning and health interventions.

